text.deposit_limit_note: Control how much you're able to deposit over a specific period of time. You won't be able to exceed your limit until the established time has passed or the limit has been reset or revoked. Our deposit limit is a net limit which counts in withdrawals made from your accounts during the time period. When you set or decrease the limit, it gets activated immediately, but if you wish to increase or revoke it, the process will take 24 hours. Daily means 00:00-23:59, Weekly means Monday-Sunday, and Monthly equals the time period starting with the 1st and ending with the last day of the month.

text.documents_address: Phone bill, bank statement in your name, or a utility bill in your name that clearly shows your full name and address.
text.documents_address_more_info: Proof of address can only be obtained by a phone bill, bank statement in your name that displays the name and address clearly.They must show your FULL address including the post/zip codes. The document must also display the official logo of the issuing company/ The bill must be dated within the last 90 days. The document should be displayed in full.
text.documents_identity_more_info: Proof of identity can only be obtained by sending a valid photo ID, passport, driving license, or any other government-issued ID. You need to send both the front and back of the ID card. The documents must not be expired (must hold valid data). The documents sent must have an expiry date. The photo on the document must not be altered in any way. Your date of birth must be clearly visible. Watermarks on the document also need to be clearly visible.
text.documents_identity_primary: Driver’s license, photo ID, passport, or other official document.
text.documents_identity_selfie_id: You can send a selfie as proof of identity with the photo ID/passport in your hands. The selfie must be a single photo that shows your face and the photo ID/passport information clearly.
text.documents_payments: For payments, you must send a copy of bank statement, screenshot from your Skrill page or any other payment method that shows the deposit.
text.documents_payments_more_info: The screenshot must show the deposit and display the company name. It must also display the amount paid.
